  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The use of country systems in countries affected by conflict and fragility: What can Denmark learn?</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of the study is to deepen the understanding of challenges and opportunities in the use of country systems to deliver aid in countries affected by conflict and fragility in order to apply the lessons learned to future Danish support. The study will focus on the experiences South Sudan, Afghanistan and two more countries.
The study will analyze how international donors approach the use of country systems in the context of fragile and conflict affected states and examine to what degree the country systems can be &#xBF; and have been &#xBF; used for delivery of aid in the spirit of the principles of the New Deal.</narrative>
  </description>
